-- Shale Gas Has ‘Great Potential’ for U.K., Energy Minister Says
-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s
-- 2012-10-16T10:14:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-16/shale-gas-has-great-potential-for-u-k-energy-minister-says.html
Britain has “great potential” to
develop shale gas fields once the governemnt gets the right
regulations in place for the industry, the nation’s energy
minister said.  John Hayes, who was named to his post last month, said,
“Once we’ve got the safety and security right, the regulations
right, shale gas has great potential for Britain.” He spoke in
an interview with Bloomberg Television in  London  today.  “This is innovative. We have to do this in a way that’s
cautious and careful,” he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Morales in London at 
